 Warm-up matches

The ICC announced the World Cup schedule on 27 June 2023 at an event in Mumbai with a countdown of 100 days to the opening match of the World Cup on 5 October. The group stage started with the match between the  finalists  of the  2019 Cricket World Cup ,  New Zealand  and  England , at  Narendra Modi Stadium . [ 8 ]  On 9 August 2023, nine fixtures, including the match between India and Pakistan, were rescheduled by the ICC. [ 40 ]  The top seven teams in the tournament, excluding Pakistan who qualify automatically as host, qualified for the  2025 ICC Champions Trophy . [ 41 ] 

